            <section class="tutorial-content">
                <div class="breadcrumb">
                    <a href="index.html">Home</a> / 
                    <a href="categories.html">Categories</a> / 
                    <a href="tutorials.html">Wooden Crafts</a> / 
                    <span>Wooden Phone Stand</span>
                </div>
                
                <h1 class="tutorial-title">Simple DIY Wooden Phone Stand (Beginner Friendly)</h1>
                
                <div class="creator-info">
                    <img src="assets/images/creator-profile.jpg" alt="Profile of Maker Mike" class="creator-photo">
                    <span class="creator-name">By <a href="community.html">Maker Mike</a></span>
                    <span class="date"><i class="fas fa-calendar-alt"></i> Published: Jan 15, 2025</span>
                </div>

                <div class="media-container">
                    
                </div>
                
                <p class="summary">
                    This is the perfect project for new woodworkers! You only need a small piece of wood and two simple cuts to create a functional and elegant phone stand for your desk or nightstand. It can be easily customized with stain or paint.
                </p>

                <div class="interaction-buttons">
                    <button class="action-btn"><i class="fas fa-heart"></i> Like (4.5K)</button>
                    <button class="action-btn"><i class="fas fa-bookmark"></i> Save</button>
                    <button class="action-btn"><i class="fas fa-share-alt"></i> Share</button>
                </div>
                
                <h2 class="section-heading">Step-by-Step Instructions</h2>
                
                <div class="steps-list">
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">1</div>
                        <div class="step-detail">
                            <h3>Measure and Mark the Wood</h3>
                            <p>Cut your wood to a size of **4" x 8" (10cm x 20cm)**. On the 8-inch side, measure 2 inches from the bottom edge and mark a line across. This marks where the slot will start.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">2</div>
                        <div class="step-detail">
                            <h3>Cut the Base Slot</h3>
                            <p>Using a **handsaw or bandsaw**, cut a groove (slot) 1/2 inch wide, starting from the marked line and going halfway through the thickness of the wood. This slot is where the phone rests.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number">3</div>
                        <div class="step-detail">
                            <h3>Sand and Finish</h3>
                            <p>Thoroughly **sand all edges and surfaces** with 120, then 220-grit sandpaper for a smooth, premium feel. Apply a natural oil finish or a pastel-colored paint to complete your stand.</p>
                            
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </section>
            
            <aside class="sidebar">
                <div class="materials-box">
                    <h2 class="section-heading"><i class="fas fa-clipboard-list"></i> Materials & Tools</h2>
                    
                    <h3>Materials Needed:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-angle-right"></i> One piece of scrap wood (e.g., pine or oak), minimum 4" x 8" x 3/4"</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-angle-right"></i> Wood glue (optional)</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-angle-right"></i> Sandpaper (120 and 220 grit)</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-angle-right"></i> Wood finish (oil, stain, or pastel paint)</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <h3>Tools Required:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-angle-right"></i> Ruler or measuring tape</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-angle-right"></i> Pencil</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-angle-right"></i> Handsaw, Jigsaw, or Bandsaw</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-angle-right"></i> Clamps (optional)</li>
                    </ul>

                    <a href="shop.html" class="btn btn-primary btn-block-shop"><i class="fas fa-shopping-basket"></i> Shop These Materials</a>
                </div>
            </aside>
